      "writtenOn": "2021-03-01T14:31:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I like ~6% improvement but I\u0027m also curious why we don\u0027t see a similar benefit using the memory pool? \n\nIs it because this can reuse the last atlas op\u0027s allocation regardless of ordering with other ops, whereas the memory pool can only reuse the last op\u0027s memory that was merged?",
      "revId": "a0765bffe95d691b6ce9c5e0f5b67daeb20deb9c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "72bf8337_52cd0914",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-01T14:34:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The direction I would prefer to go, for a general solution, is to be able to append mergeable draws to an existing op directly. This would address the performance here, and also work for rectangles. When testing this idea on the texture op, it was a drastic improvement. N drawImage calls went from an order of magnitude slower than 1 drawImageSet(with N entries) to only about 10% slower than the pre-batched call.",
      "parentUuid": "1fe17acd_67b3d58c",
      "revId": "a0765bffe95d691b6ce9c5e0f5b67daeb20deb9c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "83c1d609_d8ac715b",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-01T14:37:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As Chris\u0027 new path renderer becomes the norm, many more path ops will be combinable. Currently, some of the specialized ops are limited in what they can combine because they require the view matrix to be the same. (way down the future), when we can update uniforms within an op\u0027s execution, this can be avoided. This would also allow us to merge ops that aren\u0027t otherwise mergeable due to FP uniform state being different (even if the program is the same, e.g. gradients with different colors).\n\nI\u0027m not opposed to trying this out directly for text and learning from it, but I do think we should try and keep in mind a general solution that we can get to for all ops, once the rest of the GPU backend (path rendering, pipeline updating, etc.) can handle it.",
      "parentUuid": "72bf8337_52cd0914",
      "revId": "a0765bffe95d691b6ce9c5e0f5b67daeb20deb9c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
